<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd1e7f8a-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s4247"><num value="4247">§ 4247.</num><heading> Promulgation of regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General may promulgate any rules, regulations, or guidelines that, in the Attorney General’s judgment, are necessary and appropriate to the effective administration of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddd1e7f8b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/647/tXXV/s2594">Pub. L. 101–647, title XXV, § 2594</ref>, <date date="1990-11-29">Nov. 29, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/4906">104 Stat. 4906</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
